  "original_title": "22\u0b95\u0bcd\u0b95\u0bc1 \u0b8e\u0ba4\u0bbf\u0bb0\u0bbe\u0ba9 \u0bae\u0ba9\u0bc1\u0b95\u0bcd\u0b95\u0bb3\u0bcd: \u0baa\u0bb0\u0bbf\u0b9a\u0bc0\u0bb2\u0ba9\u0bc8 \u0ba8\u0bbf\u0bb1\u0bc8\u0bb5\u0bc1",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "Petitions against 22: Completion of consideration",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "The High Court, which completed consideration of 9 petitions challenging the 22nd Amendment Bill of the Constitution, announced today (23) that the House's interpretation of the petitions would be sent to the Speaker.",
        "The petitions filed by nine persons, including Kalanidhi Gunadasa Amarasekara, were taken up for consideration before a High Court bench comprising Chief Justice Jayantha Jayasuriya, Bhubaneka Aluvihare and Arjuna Obeysekara.",
        "At that time, President's Counsel Sanjay Rajaratnam informed the forum that the provisions of the 22nd Amendment would not take away the powers of the President but would limit the powers of the President.",
        "The court directed the petitioners to submit their written explanation related to the petitions tomorrow (24) and announced that the explanation would be sent to the Speaker soon.",
        "It is noteworthy that some clauses of the 22nd Amendment Bill are unconstitutional and petitions have been filed demanding an order to accept it through a referendum."
      ],
